Medical equipment GastroScan widely used in Russian [[gastroenterology]] centers and clinics for an esophageal and a stomach pH monitoring.<ref name=RapLRT/><ref name="UsedGS">[http://www.gastroscan.ru/gastroscan/moscow/ GastroScans in Moscow clinics], [http://www.gastroscan.ru/gastroscan/region/ GastroScans in Regions of Russia]. {{ref-ru}}</ref>

==Acidogastromonitor GastroScan-24==

The '''GastroScan-24''' is a computer acidogastromonitor for 24-h or 48-h pH monitoring for an [[esophagus]], [[stomach]] and/or [[duodenum]] and for diagnostic of [[alimentary tract]] disorders.<ref name=Tri/><ref name="G24">Functional Gastroenterology, website. [http://www.gastroscan.ru/en/gastroscan/-24/ Acidogastromonitor GastroScan<sup><U+00AE></sup>-24].</ref> 

GastroScan-24 measure the [[acidity]] in two or three points of an [[upper gastrointestinal tract]] with a frequency of once per second and saves the measured values in the recorder that the patient wears on a belt. pH catheter can be inserted to a patient transnasal or oral.

GastroScan-24 used for registration of gastroesophageal and [[Biliary reflux|duodenogastroesophageal reflux]] (GER, DGER) in patients with [[Gastroesophageal reflux disease|gastroesophageal reflux disease]] (GERD) before and after surgical treatment, [[peptic ulcer]] and other gastrointestinal disorders.<ref name="YVG24">{{cite journal |author= Yanova OB| coauthors= Vasnev OS|date= |year= 2011|month= 4|title= Results of 24-h pH monitoring in patients with gastroesophageal reflux disease before and after fundoplication|trans_title= |journal= Therapeutic Archives|volume= | issn = 1440-1746 |issue= 4 |url= http://www.medlit.ru/medeng/ta/ta11e0436.htm }}</ref><ref name="ABSG24">{{cite journal |author= Abdulganieva D.| coauthors= Belyanskaya N., Salikhov I.| date= 21| year= 2009 | month= 09| pages = A16-A17
|title= Evaluation of 24-hour pH-metry in patients with rheumatological diseases taking non-steroidal antiinfammatory drugs|trans_title= |journal= Journal of Gastroenterology and Hepatology|volume= | issn = 0040-3660 |issue= 24 |url= http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1440-1746.2009.06083_8.x/pdf }}</ref><ref name="SBM24">Serova AN, Boyarinov GA, Muratov SV, Panteleyev VL. [http://www.gastroscan.ru/literature/authors/5044 The Influence of Ozonized Solutions on the Oxyntic Function of a Stomach of Patients with Peptic Ulcer of a Bulb of a Duodenal Intestine]. Proceedings of the 15th Ozone World Congress. Oral and Poster Presentations. London, UK, 2001.</ref>

==Gastroenteromonitor GastroScan-GEM==
[[File:Gastroscan-GEM Gastroenteromonitor.jpg|Gastroenteromonitor GastroScan-GEM|right|thumb|250px]]
The '''GastroS<U+0441>an-GEM''' is a computer-based instrument designed for short or long (24-h) study of electrical activity of stomach, duodenum, [[jejunum]], [[ileum]] and [[large intestine]] and/or acidity in gastrointestinal tract.<ref name="G-GEM">Functional Gastroenterology, website.  [http://www.gastroscan.ru/en/gastroscan/-gem/ Gastroenteromonitor GastroScan<sup><U+00AE></sup>-GEM].</ref>

GastroScan-GEM used for cutaneous [[Electrogastroenterography#Cutaneous_electrogastrography|cutaneous electrogastrography]] or [[Electrogastroenterography#Electrogastroenterography|electrogastroenterography]]:
* "standard" electrogastrography (two recording sessions for 30 minutes: before and after taking of standard portions of food).<ref name="Koch">Stern RM; Koch K (2004). Handbook of electrogastrography. Oxford [Oxfordshire]: Oxford University Press. ISBN 0-19-514788-X.</ref><ref name="SmSy"/> 
* "standard" electrogastroenterography (two recording sessions for 40 minutes) used medical method designed by Viktor Al. Stupin et al.<ref name="StV">{{cite journal |author= Stupin VA |coauthors= Smirnova GO; Baglaenko MV; Siluyanov SV; Zakirov DB|date= |year= 2005 |month= 2 |title= <U+041F><U+0435><U+0440><U+0438><U+0444><U+0435><U+0440><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+044D><U+043B><U+0435><U+043A><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+0433><U+0430><U+0441><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+044D><U+043D><U+0442><U+0435><U+0440><U+043E><U+0433><U+0440><U+0430><U+0444><U+0438><U+044F> <U+0432> <U+0434><U+0438><U+0430><U+0433><U+043D><U+043E><U+0441><U+0442><U+0438><U+043A><U+0435> <U+043D><U+0430><U+0440><U+0443><U+0448><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+0439> <U+043C><U+043E><U+0442><U+043E><U+0440><U+043D><U+043E>-<U+044D><U+0432><U+0430><U+043A><U+0443><U+0430><U+0442><U+043E><U+0440><U+043D><U+043E><U+0439> <U+0444><U+0443><U+043D><U+043A><U+0446><U+0438><U+0438> <U+0436><U+0435><U+043B><U+0443><U+0434><U+043E><U+0447><U+043D><U+043E>-<U+043A><U+0438><U+0448><U+0435><U+0447><U+043D><U+043E><U+0433><U+043E> <U+0442><U+0440><U+0430><U+043A><U+0442><U+0430>  | trans_title= Peripheral Electrogastroenterography in the Diagnosis of Disorders of Motor-evacuation Function of the Gastrointestinal Tract |journal=  <U+041B><U+0435><U+0447><U+0430><U+0449><U+0438><U+0439> <U+0412><U+0440><U+0430><U+0447> [The Practitioner]) |volume= |pages= 60-62 |language= Russian |issn= 1560-5175 |url= http://www.gastroscan.ru/literature/authors/184 |quote= |ref= }}</ref> 
* 24-h cutaneous electrogastrography and electrogastroenterography.<ref name="SmSy">{{cite book |last1= Smirnova |first1= GO |last2= Siluyanov |first2= SV |authorlink2= |coauthors= |editor1-first= Stupin |editor1-last= VA |title= <U+041F><U+0435><U+0440><U+0438><U+0444><U+0435><U+0440><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+044D><U+043B><U+0435><U+043A><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+0433><U+0430><U+0441><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+044D><U+043D><U+0442><U+0435><U+0440><U+043E><U+0433><U+0440><U+0430><U+0444><U+0438><U+044F> <U+0432> <U+043A><U+043B><U+0438><U+043D><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+043E><U+0439> <U+043F><U+0440><U+0430><U+043A><U+0442><U+0438><U+043A><U+0435> |trans_title= Peripheral Electrogastroenterography in Clinical Practice |url= http://www.gastroscan.ru/literature/authors/2019 |edition= |series= |volume= |date= |year= 2009 | publisher= Medpraktika-M |location = Moscow |language= Russian |isbn= 978-5-98803-169-7 |pages= 20 }}</ref>

The GastroScan-GEM used [[non-invasive]] method of investigation electrial activity. The signal is processed and displayed on the screen itself a signal, the signal after band-pass filter corresponding to the electrical activity of a digestive tract, the result of his handling of the [[Spectrum analysis|spectral]] and [[wavelet]] analysis results. According to the study physician evaluates the activity of all digestive tract and consistency of their work. The GastroScan-GEM is intended also for selection of an individual drug therapy.<ref name="SmSy"/><ref name="StV"/>

==Acidogastrometer GastroScan-5==
[[File:PH-metry (Gastroscan-5M) in On Clinik (Moscow) .jpg|right|350px|thumb|Short-term pH-metry in On Clinic (Moscow) by GastroScan-5]] The '''GastroScan-5''' is a computer-based medical equipment designed to measure the acidity just 5 points in the digestive tract, as well as for diagnostic tests that evaluate the functional state of the upper gastrointestinal tract. The study is carried out for two to three hours, the number of examined patients at the same time can vary from 1 to 5. In the course of diagnosis is determined by the amount and concentration of [[acid]] released from human fasting and postprandial effect on acid secretion lifestyle, diet, intake of various drugs. The device helps to clarify the features of the flow of stomach, duodenum, and a host of other diseases. The program provides a display monitor pH-grams for each patient directly during the study. pH-grams are processed, the results are printed and stored in a database.<ref name=Tri/><ref name="G5">Functional Gastroenterology, website. [http://www.gastroscan.ru/en/gastroscan/-5m/ Acidogastrometer GastroScan<sup><U+00AE></sup>-5].</ref>

==Gastromanometer GastroScan-D==
[[File:Example of manometry by means of Gastroscan-D.jpg|right|250px|thumb|Graphs of pressure in different parts of the esophagus during swallowing, obtained by GastroScan-D]]The '''GastroScan-D''' is a computer-based medical device designed to measure the [[pressure]] in the digestive tract by means of an 8-channel water-perfusion catheter. For each channel catheter is passed fluid at a rate of 0.5 ml per minute and flows out through openings in the side wall of the catheter. The pressure of the liquid column is transferred to the sensor is measured and displayed on the monitor screen. Pressure measurement is performed in the range from 0 to 225 [[mmHg]] with an accuracy of 3 mmHg simultaneously in different parts of the digestive tract, defined outlets (ports) channel catheter. The study is conducted for about 30 minutes. As a result, the monitor can see the wave of reduction of the esophagus, both direct and inverse, to assess the efficiency of the [[sphincter]], reducing the stomach to follow. The GastroScan-D is used to study the [[sphincter of Oddi]], and contractility of [[Colon (anatomy)|colon]] and [[rectum]] too.<ref name="GD">Functional Gastroenterology, website. [http://www.gastroscan.ru/en/gastroscan/-d/ Gastromanometer GastroScan<sup><U+00AE></sup>-D].</ref><ref name="BoVa">{{cite book |last1= Bordin |first1= DS |last2= Valitova |first2= ER |editor1-first= LB |editor1-last= Lazebnik |title= <U+041C><U+0435><U+0442><U+043E><U+0434><U+0438><U+043A><U+0430> <U+043F><U+0440><U+043E><U+0432><U+0435><U+0434><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+044F> <U+0438> <U+043A><U+043B><U+0438><U+043D><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+043E><U+0435> <U+0437><U+043D><U+0430><U+0447><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+0435> <U+043C><U+0430><U+043D><U+043E><U+043C><U+0435><U+0442><U+0440><U+0438><U+0438> <U+043F><U+0438><U+0449><U+0435><U+0432><U+043E><U+0434><U+0430> (<U+041C><U+0435><U+0442><U+043E><U+0434><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+0438><U+0435> <U+0440><U+0435><U+043A><U+043E><U+043C><U+0435><U+043D><U+0434><U+0430><U+0446><U+0438><U+0438> <U+2116> 50) |trans_title= Methodology and clinical significance of esophageal manometry (Guidelines number 50) |url= http://www.gastroscan.ru/literature/authors/2263 |year= 2009 | publisher= Medpraktika-M |location = Moscow |language= Russian |isbn= 978-5-98803-172-7 |pages= 24 }}</ref><ref name="StoTr">{{cite book |last1= Storonova |first1= OA |last2= Trukhmanov |first2= AS |authorlink2= |coauthors= |editor1-first= VT |editor1-last= Ivashkin |title= <U+041C><U+0435><U+0442><U+043E><U+0434><U+0438><U+043A><U+0430> <U+0438><U+0437><U+0443><U+0447><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+044F> <U+0434><U+0432><U+0438><U+0433><U+0430><U+0442><U+0435><U+043B><U+044C><U+043D><U+043E><U+0439> <U+0444><U+0443><U+043D><U+043A><U+0446><U+0438><U+0438> <U+043F><U+0438><U+0449><U+0435><U+0432><U+043E><U+0434><U+0430> |trans_title= The method of studying esophageal motor function |url= http://www.gastroscan.ru/literature/authors/4445 |year= 2011 | publisher= Medpraktika-M |location = Moscow |language= Russian |isbn= 978-5-98803-236-6 |pages= 36 }}</ref>

